Bachata is a style of social dance from the Dominician Republic which is now danced all over the world. Dancers are paired as couples to perform the dance, and to look visually appealing, the pair is usually made of people of similar height.

Alice runs a dance academy, and for her new Bachata batch, a lot of dancers have registered. She now has to pair them into couples and decides that a couple can differ in height by no more than 2 inches. Any person who can't fit into such a couple has to leave. Alice wants to give higher priority to the participants of smaller height to form a couple. If more than one choice is available to form a couple, then the priority is given to participants arriving earlier i.e. first come first serve' principle is applied.

Write a program to help Alice form the pairs, given the number of participants n, and the name and height of each participant.

Read the input from STDIN and print the output to STDOUT. Do not write arbitrary strings while reading the input or while printing, as these contribute to the standard output.

Input Format

The first line of input contains a single integer T, denoting the number of test cases. Then the test cases follow.

Each test case:
The first line contains a single integer N, denoting the number of participants, then N lines follow.

Each line has a string and an integer, S and X, space-separated, denoting the name and height respectively.

Output Format

Output n/2 lines, each line containing two strings with the names of the couple. Note that the height of the first person should be less than the height of the second person and if they are equal the first person should have arrived earlier.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10^5

1 ≤ n ≤ 10^4

20 ≤ Hi ≤ 200

Sum of all n ≤ 10^6 over all test cases

Sample Input 1

1
4
Sam 60
Dan 52
Bob 54
Art 61

Sample Output 1

Dan Bob
Sam Art

Sample Input 2

1
4
Sam 50
Dan 50
Bob 50
Art 50

Sample Output 2

Sam Dan
Bob Art

Sample Input 3

1
4
Rock 52
Sam 51
Dan 62
Art 61

Sample Output 3

Sam Rock
Art Dan

Note

In the first example, Dan and Bob are paired as height is the first priority. Then Sam and Art are paired. The orders are chosen on the same priority first on height than on the time of arrival. (first come first serve)



Time Complexity: O(nlogn)
Space Complexity:  O(n)


#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl


bool comp(pair<int,pair<string,int>> &a, pair<int,pair<string,int>> &b)
{
    if(a.second.second !=  b.second.second)
    {
        return a.second.second < b.second.second;
    }

    return a.first < b.first;

}
void solve() {
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    vector<pair<int,pair<string,int>>>v;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        string a;
        int b;
        cin>>a>>b;
        v.push_back({i,{a,b}});
    }

    sort(v.begin(),v.end(),comp);

    vector<pair<string,string>> ans;


    int i = 0;
    while(i < n - 1)
    {
        int h1 = v[i].second.second;
        int h2 = v[i+1].second.second;

        if(h2 - h1 <= 2)
        {
            ans.push_back({v[i].second.first, v[i+1].second.first});
            i += 2;
        }
        else
        {
            i++;
        }
    }
    


    for(auto it : ans)
    {
        cout<<it.first<<" "<<it.second<<endl;
    }
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}



